from most biomes. Integration of range-wide population trajectories and size estimates indicates a net loss approaching 3 billion birds, or 29% of 1970 abundance. A continent-wide weather radar network also reveals a similarly steep decline in biomass passage of migrating birds over a recent 10-year period. This loss of bird abundance signals an urgent need to address threats to avert future avifaunal collapse and associated loss of ecosystem integrity, function, and services.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Rosenberg, Kenneth V.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dokter, Adriaan M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Blancher, Peter J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sauer, John R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Smith, Adam C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Smith, Paul A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Stanton, Jessica C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Panjabi, Arvind", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Helft, Laura", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Parr, Michael", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Marra, Peter P.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/a5c5eb813165c3d353fe52bebfeadb29", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/c23daa54b4060bb4c546cb35c63d9ad72b465b485972f7943ee19a6c86d22e1d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/WS5DWQGB", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/WS5DWQGB", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/7dec04465d933ebfaa8af17134faffaf!/b245075-247512", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "r